  "local_port": 37056,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you reduce the magnification of your screen?",
  "response": "To reduce the magnification of your screen, you can follow these steps based on your operating system:\n\n### Windows:\n1. **Using Keyboard Shortcuts:**\n   - Press `Ctrl` + `-` (minus key) to zoom out in most applications.\n   - Press `Windows` + `Esc` to exit Magnifier if it's open.\n\n2. **Using Magnifier:**\n   - If you have the Magnifier tool open, you can click the `-` button to zoom out.\n\n3. **Display Settings:**\n   - Right-click on the desktop and select **Display settings**.\n   - Under **Scale and layout**, adjust the scaling percentage to a lower value.\n\n### macOS:\n1. **Using Keyboard Shortcuts:**\n   - Press `Command` + `Option` + `-` (minus key) to zoom out if zoom is enabled.\n\n2. **System Preferences:**\n   - Go to **System Preferences** > **Displays**.\n   - Adjust the **Resolution** settings or the **Scaled** options to change the display size.\n\n### Web Browsers:\n1. **Zoom Out:**\n   - Press `Ctrl` + `-` (Windows) or `Command` + `-` (Mac) to reduce zoom level.\n   - You can also go to the browser's menu (three dots or lines) and find the zoom options there.\n\n### Mobile Devices:\n1. **iOS:**\n   - Open **Settings** > **Display & Brightness** > **View** and select a smaller display size.\n   - For accessibility zoom, double-tap with three fingers and then drag down to zoom out.\n\n2. **Android:**\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Display** > **Screen zoom** and adjust the slider.\n   - For accessibility zoom, go to **Settings** > **Accessibility** > **Magnification** and turn it off or adjust settings.\n\nThese methods should help you reduce the magnification of your screen.",
